Heat grill. Divide turkey evenly into 4 balls. Press 2 teaspoons butter in center of each ball. Form balls into 5 to 6-inch diameter patties. Season with salt and pepper, if you like. Place burgers on grill over medium heat. Cover and cook 6 to 8 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, turning once. Place burgers on buns; top with onion, tomato and lettuce.